results.name: Right Moebius transformation matrix, M, by antidiagonals.
comment: If S=(s(1),s(2),...) is a sequence written as a row vector, then S*M is the Moebius transform of S; i.e. its n-th term is Sum{mu(k)*s(k): k|n}. M is the transpose of the left Moebius transformation matrix, A077050.
formula: M=T^(-1), where T is the right summatory matrix, A077051.
results.author: _Clark Kimberling_, Oct 22 2002
